00:00:08.745 --> 00:00:13.749
by the dozen now. That does mean, though, that depending on how many nozzles he

00:00:13.749 --> 00:00:18.930
has total, he might have some left over. For example, if Grant has 40 nozzles

00:00:18.930 --> 00:00:25.267
total, then that will make 3 and 1 3rd packages of 12 nozzles. Since if we take

00:00:25.267 --> 00:00:29.398
40 and divide it by 12, we get 3 and a 3rd. And we can see these 3 whole

00:00:29.398 --> 00:00:34.900
